# Implement "Demo Expired" Page

This plan replaces the live site content with a professional "Demo Expired" page as a sales tactic to maintain control over assets and signal professionalism.

## Proposed Changes

### [Jelani Motors Core]

#### [NEW] [DemoExpired.jsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Documents/WEB%20DEV/01_CLIENT_WORK/Jelani_Motors/src/components/DemoExpired.jsx)
Create a new component with a clean, centered, corporate-looking message.
- Use [LogoSVG](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Documents/WEB%20DEV/01_CLIENT_WORK/Jelani_Motors/src/components/ui.jsx#60-71) for branding.
- Include "Prototype Access Expired" heading.
- Include the descriptive text provided by the user.
- Add a "Contact Benard on WhatsApp" button with a professional pre-filled message.

#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Documents/WEB%20DEV/01_CLIENT_WORK/Jelani_Motors/src/App.jsx)
- Import `DemoExpired` from `./components/DemoExpired`.
- At the top of the component (or after minimal necessary setup), return `<DemoExpired />` to prevent the rest of the app from rendering.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Run `npm run dev` and navigate to the local site.
- Verify that the "Demo Expired" page is the only thing rendered.
- Verify that the page is centered and looks professional on both desktop and mobile.
- Click the "Contact Benard on WhatsApp" button to verify the link and pre-filled message.
